cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.CE, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a distributed controller for frequency control in a power system, which involves control and optimization techniques. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on a decentralized and distributed approach for frequency control, which involves communication and coordination among different control areas. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper may involve programming languages for implementing the proposed controller and simulation experiments. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper may involve computational methods for solving the optimization problem and analyzing the closed-loop system. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper may involve performance analysis of the proposed controller in terms of stability, convergence, and robustness.
